AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:IdentifiedObject
AFElementTemplate.Description: This is a root class to provide common naming attributes for all classes needing naming attributes

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IdentifiedObject.aliasName
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The aliasName is free text human readable name of the object alternative to IdentifiedObject.name. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IdentifiedObject.description
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The description is a free human readable text describing or naming the object. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IdentifiedObject.localName
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The localName is a human readable name of the object. It is only used with objects organized in a naming hierarchy. The simplest naming hierarchy has just one parent (the root) giving a flat naming hierarchy. However, the naming hierarchy usually has several levels, e.g. Substation, VoltageLevel, Equipment etc. Children of the same parent have names that are unique among them. If the uniqueness requirement cannot be met IdentifiedObject.localName shall not be used, use IdentifiedObject.name instead.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IdentifiedObject.mRID
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: A Model Authority issues mRIDs. Given that each Model Authority has a unique id and this id is part of the mRID, then the mRID is globally unique.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IdentifiedObject.name
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The name is a free text human readable name of the object. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IdentifiedObject.pathName
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The pathname is a system unique name composed from all IdentifiedObject.localNames in a naming hierarchy path from the object to the root.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:AccessPoint
AFElementTemplate.Description: Used to represent the AccessPoint information from IEC 61850.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:PowerSystemResource
AFElementTemplate.Description: A power system resource can be an item of equipment such as a Switch, an EquipmentContainer containing many individual items of equipment such as a Substation, or an organisational entity such as Company or SubControlArea. This provides for the nesting of collections of PowerSystemResources within other PowerSystemResources. For example, a Switch could be a member of a Substation and a Substation could be a member of a division of a Company.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:Equipment
AFElementTemplate.Description: The parts of a power system that are physical devices, electronic or mechanical

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:ConductingEquipment
AFElementTemplate.Description: The parts of the power system that are designed to carry current or that are conductively connected therewith. ConductingEquipment is contained within an EquipmentContainer that may be a Substation, or a VoltageLevel or a Bay within a Substation.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:Conductor
AFElementTemplate.Description: Combination of conducting material with consistent electrical characteristics, building a single electrical system, used to carry current between points in the power system.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Conductor.bch
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence shunt (charging) susceptance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Conductor.r
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence series resistance of the entire line section.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Conductor.x
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence series reactance of the entire line section.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:ACLineSegment
AFElementTemplate.Description: A wire or combination of wires, with consistent electrical characteristics, building a single electrical system, used to carry alternating current between points in the power system.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:OperationalLimit
AFElementTemplate.Description: A value associated with a specific kind of limit.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: OperationalLimit.type
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Used to specify high/low and limit levels.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:ActivePowerLimit
AFElementTemplate.Description: Limit on active power flow.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ActivePowerLimit.value
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Value of active power limit.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:Measurement
AFElementTemplate.Description: A Measurement represents any measured, calculated or non-measured non-calculated quantity. Any piece of equipment may contain Measurements, e.g. a substation may have temperature measurements and door open indications, a transformer may have oil temperature and tank pressure measurements, a bay may contain a number of power flow measurements and a Breaker may contain a switch status measurement. The PSR - Measurement association is intended to capture this use of Measurement and is included in the naming hierarchy based on EquipmentContainer. The naming hierarchy typically has Measurements as leafs, e.g. Substation-VoltageLevel-Bay-Switch-Measurement. Some Measurements represent quantities related to a particular sensor location in the network, e.g. a voltage transformer (PT) at a busbar or a current transformer (CT) at the bar between a breaker and an isolator. The sensing position is not captured in the PSR - Measurement association. Instead it is captured by the Measurement - Term

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:Analog
AFElementTemplate.Description: Analog represents an analog Measurement.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Analog.positiveFlowIn
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: If true then this measurement is an active power, reactive power or current with the convention that a positive value measured at the Terminal means power is flowing into the related PowerSystemResource.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:MeasurementValue
AFElementTemplate.Description: The current state for a measurement. A state value is an instance of a measurement from a specific source. Measurements can be associated with many state values, each representing a different source for the measurement.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:AnalogValue
AFElementTemplate.Description: AnalogValue represents an analog MeasurementValue.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: AnalogValue.value
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The value to supervise.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:ApparentPowerLimit
AFElementTemplate.Description: Apparent power limit.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ApparentPowerLimit.value
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The apparent power limit.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:Authentication
AFElementTemplate.Description: Still needs definition and is part of future work.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:BaseVoltage
AFElementTemplate.Description: Collection of BaseVoltages which is used to verify that the BusbarSection.BaseVoltage and other voltage attributes in the CIM are given a value existing in the collection.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: BaseVoltage.nominalVoltage
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The PowerSystemResource's base voltage.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:BasicIntervalSchedule
AFElementTemplate.Description: Schedule of values at points in time.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: BasicIntervalSchedule.startTime
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The time for the first time point.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: BasicIntervalSchedule.value1Unit
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Value1 units of measure.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: BasicIntervalSchedule.value2Unit
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Value2 units of measure.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:ConnectivityNodeContainer
AFElementTemplate.Description: A base class for all objects that may contain ConnectivityNodes.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:EquipmentContainer
AFElementTemplate.Description: A modeling construct to provide a root class for all Equipment classes

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:Bay
AFElementTemplate.Description: A collection of power system resources (within a given substation) including conducting equipment, protection relays, measurements, and telemetry.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:Switch
AFElementTemplate.Description: A generic device designed to close, or open, or both, one or more electric circuits.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Switch.normalOpen
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The attribute is used in cases when no Measurement for the status value is present. If the Switch has a status measurment the Discrete.normalValue is expected to match with the Switch.normalOpen.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:Breaker
AFElementTemplate.Description: A mechanical switching device capable of making, carrying, and breaking currents under normal circuit conditions and also making, carrying for a specified time, and breaking currents under specified abnormal circuit conditions e.g. those of short circuit.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Breaker.ratedCurrent
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Fault interrupting current rating.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:BusbarSection
AFElementTemplate.Description: A conductor, or group of conductors, with negligible impedance, that serve to connect other conducting equipment within a single substation. Voltage measurements are typically obtained from VoltageTransformers that are connected to busbar sections. A bus bar section may have many physical terminals but for analysis is modelled with exactly one logical terminal.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:RemoteUnit
AFElementTemplate.Description: A remote unit can be a RTU, IED, substation control system, control center etc. The communication with the remote unit can be through various standard protocols (e.g. IEC 61870, IEC 61850) or non standard protocols (e.g. DNP, RP570 etc.). A remote unit contain remote data points that might be telemetered, collected or calculated. The RemoteUnit class inherit PowerSystemResource. The intention is to allow RemotUnits to have Measurements. These Measurements can be used to model unit status as operational, out of service, unit failure etc.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IED.configVersion
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Configuration version of the IED.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IED.manufacturer
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Name of the IED Manufacturer

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IED.type
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Type of IED

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:CommunicationLink
AFElementTemplate.Description: The connection to remote units is through one or more communication links. Reduntant links may exist. The CommunicationLink class inherit PowerSystemResource. The intention is to allow CommunicationLinks to have Measurements. These Measurements can be used to model link status as operational, out of service, unit failure etc.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: CommunicationLink.ProtocolInUse
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Identifier of the Communication protocol to be used (e.g. Modbus, DNP, 61850, GOOSE, SV, etc..). This attribute was explicitly made a string so as to allow easy expansion.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:EnergyConsumer
AFElementTemplate.Description: Generic user of energy - a point of consumption on the power system model

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: EnergyConsumer.pfixed
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Active power of the load that is a fixed quantity.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: EnergyConsumer.pfixedPct
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Fixed active power as per cent of load group fixed active power

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: EnergyConsumer.qfixed
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Reactive power of the load that is a fixed quantity.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: EnergyConsumer.qfixedPct
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Fixed reactive power as per cent of load group fixed reactive power.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:ConformLoad
AFElementTemplate.Description: ConformLoad represent loads that follow a daily load change pattern where the pattern can be used to scale the load with a system load.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:LoadGroup
AFElementTemplate.Description: The class is the third level in a hierarchical structure for grouping of loads for the purpose of load flow load scaling.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:ConformLoadGroup
AFElementTemplate.Description: Load that follows a daily and seasonal load variation pattern.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:RegularIntervalSchedule
AFElementTemplate.Description: The schedule has TimePoints where the time between them is constant.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RegularIntervalSchedule.endTime
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The time for the last time point.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RegularIntervalSchedule.timeStep
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The time between each pair of subsequent RegularTimePoints.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:SeasonDayTypeSchedule
AFElementTemplate.Description: The schedule specialize RegularIntervalSchedule with type curve data for a specific type of day and season. This means that curves of this type cover a 24 hour period.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:ConformLoadSchedule
AFElementTemplate.Description: A curve of load versus time (X-axis) showing the active power values (Y1-axis) and reactive power (Y2-axis) for each unit of the period covered. This curve represents a typical pattern of load over the time period for a given day type and season.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:ConnectivityNode
AFElementTemplate.Description: Connectivity nodes are points where terminals of conducting equipment are connected together with zero impedance.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:ControlArea
AFElementTemplate.Description: A control area is a grouping of generating units and/or loads and a cutset of tie lines (as terminals) which may be used for a variety of purposes including automatic generation control, powerflow solution area interchange control specification, and input to load forecasting. Note that any number of overlapping control area specifications can be superimposed on the physical model.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ControlArea.netInterchange
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The specified positive net interchange into the control area.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ControlArea.type
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The type of control area defintion used to determine if this is used for automatic generation control, for planning interchange control, or other purposes.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:ControlAreaGeneratingUnit
AFElementTemplate.Description: A control area generating unit. This class is needed so that alternate control area definitions may include the same generating unit. Note only one instance within a control area should reference a specific generating unit.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:CurrentLimit
AFElementTemplate.Description: OIoeratuibak kimit on current.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: CurrentLimit.value
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Limit on current flow.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:Curve
AFElementTemplate.Description: Relationship between an independent variable (X-axis) and one or two dependent variables (Y1-axis and Y2-axis). Curves can also serve as schedules.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Curve.curveStyle
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The style or shape of the curve.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Curve.xUnit
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The X-axis units of measure.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Curve.y1Unit
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The Y1-axis units of measure.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Curve.y2Unit
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The Y2-axis units of measure.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:CurveData
AFElementTemplate.Description: Data point values for defining a curve or schedule

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: CurveData.xvalue
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The data value of the X-axis variable, depending on the X-axis units

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: CurveData.y1value
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The data value of the first Y-axis variable, depending on the Y-axis units

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: CurveData.y2value
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The data value of the second Y-axis variable (if present), depending on the Y-axis units

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:CustomerLoad
AFElementTemplate.Description: A meter for measuring customer energy consumption. The typeName attribute indicates the type of customer meter.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:DayType
AFElementTemplate.Description: Group of similar days, e.g., Mon/Tue/Wed, Thu/Fri, Sat/Sun, Holiday1, Holiday2

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:Disconnector
AFElementTemplate.Description: A manually operated or motor operated mechanical switching device used for changing the connections in a circuit, or for isolating a circuit or equipment from a source of power. It is required to open or close circuits when negligible current is broken or made.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:Discrete
AFElementTemplate.Description: Discrete represents a discrete Measurement, i.e. a Measurement reprsenting discrete values, e.g. a Breaker position.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:DiscreteValue
AFElementTemplate.Description: DiscreteValue represents a discrete MeasurementValue.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: DiscreteValue.value
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The value to supervise.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:EnergyArea
AFElementTemplate.Description: The class describes an area having energy production or consumption. The class is the basis for further specialization.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:EquivalentEquipment
AFElementTemplate.Description: The class represents equivalent objects that are the result of a network reduction. The class is the base for equivalent objects of diferent types.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:EquivalentBranch
AFElementTemplate.Description: The class represents equivalent branches.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: EquivalentBranch.r
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence series resistance of the reduced branch.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: EquivalentBranch.x
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence series reactance of the reduced branch.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:EquivalentNetwork
AFElementTemplate.Description: A class that represents an external meshed network that has been reduced to an electrically equivalent model. The ConnectivityNodes contained in the equivalent are intended to reflect internal nodes of the equivalent. The boundary Connectivity nodes where the equivalent connects outside itself are NOT contained by the equivalent.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:EquivalentShunt
AFElementTemplate.Description: The class represents equivalent shunts.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: EquivalentShunt.b
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence shunt susceptance.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: EquivalentShunt.g
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence shunt conductance.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Layer2_AccessPoint.IEEE_Priority
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Specifies the Ethernet Priority Tag value. The appropriate values are defined in IEEE 802.1P

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Layer2_AccessPoint.MAC_Address
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: IEEE Media Access Address

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Layer2_AccessPoint.VLAN_ID
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Specifies the value for an Ethernet VLAN ID. Valid values are specified in IEEE 802.1Q.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Ethertype.Ethertype
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Specifies the IEEE assigned Etherype that represents the protocol.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:FFT
AFElementTemplate.Description: A specialized calculated value that contains FFT bays

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:GeneratingUnit
AFElementTemplate.Description: A single or set of synchronous machines for converting mechanical power into alternating-current power. For example, individual machines within a set may be defined for scheduling purposes while a single control signal is derived for the set. In this case there would be a GeneratingUnit for each member of the set and an additional GeneratingUnit corresponding to the set.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: GeneratingUnit.genControlSource
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The source of controls for a generating unit.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: GeneratingUnit.initialP
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Default Initial active power which is used to store a powerflow result for the initial active power for this unit in this network configuration

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: GeneratingUnit.longPF
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Generating unit economic participation factor

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: GeneratingUnit.maxOperatingP
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: This is the maximum operating active power limit the dispatcher can enter for this unit

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: GeneratingUnit.minOperatingP
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: This is the minimum operating active power limit the dispatcher can enter for this unit.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: GeneratingUnit.normalPF
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Generating unit economic participation factor

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: GeneratingUnit.ratedGrossMaxP
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The unit's gross rated maximum capacity (Book Value).

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: GeneratingUnit.ratedGrossMinP
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The gross rated minimum generation level which the unit can safely operate at while delivering power to the transmission grid

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: GeneratingUnit.ratedNetMaxP
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The net rated maximum capacity determined by subtracting the auxiliary power used to operate the internal plant machinery from the rated gross maximum capacity

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: GeneratingUnit.shortPF
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Generating unit economic participation factor

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:GeographicalRegion
AFElementTemplate.Description: A geographical region of a power system network model.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:GrossToNetActivePowerCurve
AFElementTemplate.Description: Relationship between the generating unit's gross active power output on the X-axis (measured at the terminals of the machine(s)) and the generating unit's net active power output on the Y-axis (based on utility-defined measurements at the power station). Station service loads, when modeled, should be treated as non-conforming bus loads. There may be more than one curve, depending on the auxiliary equipment that is in service.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:HydroGeneratingUnit
AFElementTemplate.Description: A generating unit whose prime mover is a hydraulic turbine (e.g., Francis, Pelton, Kaplan)

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:IEC61970CIMVersion
AFElementTemplate.Description: This is the IEC 61970 CIM version number assigned to this UML model file.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IPv4_AccessPoint.IPAddress
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: IP Address to which packets need to be sent. The value shall be either xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx or Hostname format.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IPv4_AccessPoint.IP-Gateway
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: IP Gateway for the next hop information for the IP Address/Subnet mask combination.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IPv4_AccessPoint.IP-Subnet
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: IP Subnet mask. The mask shall be in the format of xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: UDP_AccessPoint.port
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Specifies the UDP port to which packets need to be sent.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:IEC870-5ofDNPUdpAccessPoint
AFElementTemplate.Description: Deprecated for Future use.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IEC870-5ofDNPUdpAccessPoint.OutStationID
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Specifies the DNP Slave Address

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TCP_AccessPoint.KeeoAliveTime
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: TCP Keepalive time specified in Seconds.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TCP_AccessPoint.Port
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Specifies the TCP port to which the TCP_OPEN needs to be sent.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IEC870-5orDNPTcpAccessPoint.OutStationID
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Specifies the DNP Slave Address

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:NonConformLoad
AFElementTemplate.Description: NonConformLoad represent loads that do not follow a daily load change pattern and changes are not correlated with the daily load change pattern.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:InductionMotorLoad
AFElementTemplate.Description: Large three phase induction motor load. The typeName attribute indicates the type of induction motor (1 = wound rotor) (2 = squirrel cage).

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:ISOUpperLayer
AFElementTemplate.Description: Can be used to address ICCP or 61850

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ISOUpperLayer.AP
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: DT:ISOAPAddressing

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ISOUpperLayer.OSI-PSEL
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Specifies the OSI Presentation Selector. The format shall be continuos hexadecimal values.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ISOUpperLayer.OSI-SSEL
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Specifies the OSI Session Selector. The format shall be continuos hexadecimal values.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ISOUpperLayer.OSI-TSEL
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Specifies the OSI Transport Selector. The format shall be continuos hexadecimal values.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:LimitSet
AFElementTemplate.Description: Specifies a set of Limits that are associated with a Measurement. A Measurement may have several LimitSets corresponding to seasonal or other changing conditions. The condition is captured in the name and description attributes. The same LimitSet may be used for several Measurements. In particular percentage limits are used this way.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: LimitSet.isPercentageLimits
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Tells if the limit values are in percentage of normalValue or the specified Unit for Measurements and Controls.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:Line
AFElementTemplate.Description: A component part of a system extending between adjacent substations or from a substation to an adjacent interconnection point.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:Load
AFElementTemplate.Description: A generic equivalent for an energy consumer on a transmission or distribution voltage level. It may be under load management and also has cold load pick up characteristics.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:LoadArea
AFElementTemplate.Description: The class is the root or first level in a hierarchical structure for grouping of loads for the purpose of load flow load scaling.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:LoadBreakSwitch
AFElementTemplate.Description: A mechanical switching device capable of making, carrying, and breaking currents under normal operating conditions.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: LoadBreakSwitch.ratedCurrent
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Current carrying capacity of a wire or cable under stated thermal conditions.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:LoadResponseCharacteristic
AFElementTemplate.Description: Models the characteristic response of the load demand due to to changes in system conditions such as voltage and frequency. This is not related to demand response.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: LoadResponseCharacteristic.pFrequencyExponent
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Exponent of per unit frequency effecting active power

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: LoadResponseCharacteristic.pVoltageExponent
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Exponent of per unit voltage effecting real power. This model used only when "useExponentModel" is true.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: LoadResponseCharacteristic.qFrequencyExponent
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Exponent of per unit frequency effecting reactive power

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: LoadResponseCharacteristic.qVoltageExponent
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Exponent of per unit voltage effecting reactive power. This model used only when "useExponentModel" is true.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:MeasurementType
AFElementTemplate.Description: Specifies the type of Measurement, e.g. IndoorTemperature, OutDoorTemperature, BusVoltage, GeneratorVoltage, LineFlow etc. The MeasurementType.name shall be unique among all specified types and describe the type. The MeasurementType.aliasName is meant to be used for localization.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:MeasurementValueSource
AFElementTemplate.Description: MeasurementValueSource describes the alternative sources updating a MeasurementValue. User conventions for how to use the MeasurementValueSource attributes are described in the introduction to IEC 61970-301.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:NonConformLoadGroup
AFElementTemplate.Description: Loads that do not follow a daily and seasonal load variation pattern.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:NonConformLoadSchedule
AFElementTemplate.Description: An active power (Y1-axis) and reactive power (Y2-axis) schedule (curves) versus time (X-axis) for non-conforming loads, e.g., large industrial load or power station service (where modeled)

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:OperationalLimitSet
AFElementTemplate.Description: A set of limits associated with equipmnet.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:PMU_Template_Base
AFElementTemplate.Description: A specialized IED that emits Synchrophasor information

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:PMU
AFElementTemplate.Description: A specialized IED that emits Synchrophasor information

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: PMU.Latitude
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Geospatial Latitude

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: PMU.Longitude
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Geospatial Longitue

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:PowerTransformer
AFElementTemplate.Description: An electrical device consisting of two or more coupled windings, with or without a magnetic core, for introducing mutual coupling between electric circuits. Transformers can be used to control voltage and phase shift (active power flow).

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:ReactiveCapabilityCurve
AFElementTemplate.Description: Reactive power rating envelope versus the synchronous machine's active power, in both the generating and motoring modes. For each active power value there is a corresponding high and low reactive power limit value. Typically there will be a separate curve for each coolant condition, such as hydrogen pressure. The Y1 axis values represent reactive minimum and the Y2 axis values represent reactive maximum.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:RegularTimePoint
AFElementTemplate.Description: TimePoints for a schedule where the time between the points is constant.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RegularTimePoint.sequenceNumber
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The position of the RegularTimePoint in the sequence. Note that time points don't have to be sequential, i.e. time points may be omitted. The actual time for a RegularTimePoint is computed by multiplying the RegularIntervalSchedule.timeStep with the RegularTimePoint.sequenceNumber and add the BasicIntervalSchedule.startTime.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RegularTimePoint.value1
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The first value at the time. The meaning of the value is defined by the class inhering the RegularIntervalSchedule.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RegularTimePoint.value2
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The second value at the time. The meaning of the value is defined by the class inhering the RegularIntervalSchedule.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:RegulatingCondEq
AFElementTemplate.Description: RegulatingCondEq is a type of ConductingEquipment that can regulate Measurements and have a RegulationSchedule.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:RegulatingControl
AFElementTemplate.Description: Specifies a set of equipment that works together to control a power system quantity such as voltage or flow.

AFElementTemplate.Name: demo:StaticVarCompensator
AFElementTemplate.Description: A facility for providing variable and controllable shunt reactive power. The SVC typically consists of a stepdown transformer, filter, thyristor-controlled reactor, and thyristor-switched capacitor arms. The SVC may operate in fixed MVar output mode or in voltage control mode. When in voltage control mode, the output of the SVC will be proportional to the deviation of voltage at the controlled bus from the voltage setpoint. The SVC characteristic slope defines the proportion. If the voltage at the controlled bus is equal to the voltage setpoint, the SVC MVar output is zero.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: StaticVarCompensator.inductiveRating

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: StaticVarCompensator.slope
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The characteristics slope of an SVC defines how the reactive power output changes in proportion to the difference between the regulated bus voltage and the voltage setpoint.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: StaticVarCompensator.sVCControlMode
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: SVC control mode.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: StaticVarCompensator.voltageSetPoint
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The reactive power output of the SVC is proportional to the difference between the voltage at the regulated bus and the voltage setpoint. When the regulated bus voltage is equal to the voltage setpoint, the reactive power output is zero.

Note that any number of overlapping control area specifications can be superimposed on the physical model.

AFElement.Name: LimitSet
AFElement.Description: Specifies a set of Limits that are associated with a Measurement. A Measurement may have several LimitSets corresponding to seasonal or other changing conditions. The condition is captured in the name and description attributes. The same LimitSet may be used for several Measurements. In particular percentage limits are used this way.

AFElement.Name: Line
AFElement.Description: A component part of a system extending between adjacent substations or from a substation to an adjacent interconnection point.

AFElement.Name: Load
AFElement.Description: A generic equivalent for an energy consumer on a transmission or distribution voltage level. It may be under load management and also has cold load pick up characteristics.

AFElement.Name: LoadArea
AFElement.Description: The class is the root or first level in a hierarchical structure for grouping of loads for the purpose of load flow load scaling.

AFElement.Name: LoadBreakSwitch
AFElement.Description: A mechanical switching device capable of making, carrying, and breaking currents under normal operating conditions.

AFElement.Name: LoadGroup
AFElement.Description: The class is the third level in a hierarchical structure for grouping of loads for the purpose of load flow load scaling.

AFElement.Name: LoadResponseCharacteristic
AFElement.Description: Models the characteristic response of the load demand due to to changes in system conditions such as voltage and frequency. This is not related to demand response.

AFElement.Name: Measurement
AFElement.Description: A Measurement represents any measured, calculated or non-measured non-calculated quantity. Any piece of equipment may contain Measurements, e.g. a substation may have temperature measurements and door open indications, a transformer may have oil temperature and tank pressure measurements, a bay may contain a number of power flow measurements and a Breaker may contain a switch status measurement. The PSR - Measurement association is intended to capture this use of Measurement and is included in the naming hierarchy based on EquipmentContainer. The naming hierarchy typically has Measurements as leafs, e.g. Substation-VoltageLevel-Bay-Switch-Measurement. Some Measurements represent quantities related to a particular sensor location in the network, e.g. a voltage transformer (PT) at a busbar or a current transformer (CT) at the bar between a breaker and an isolator. The sensing position is not captured in the PSR - Measurement association. Instead it is captured by the Measurement - Term

AFElement.Name: MeasurementType
AFElement.Description: Specifies the type of Measurement, e.g. IndoorTemperature, OutDoorTemperature, BusVoltage, GeneratorVoltage, LineFlow etc. The MeasurementType.name shall be unique among all specified types and describe the type. The MeasurementType.aliasName is meant to be used for localization.

AFElement.Name: MeasurementValue
AFElement.Description: The current state for a measurement. A state value is an instance of a measurement from a specific source. Measurements can be associated with many state values, each representing a different source for the measurement.

AFElement.Name: MeasurementValueSource
AFElement.Description: MeasurementValueSource describes the alternative sources updating a MeasurementValue. User conventions for how to use the MeasurementValueSource attributes are described in the introduction to IEC 61970-301.

AFElement.Name: NonConformLoad
AFElement.Description: NonConformLoad represent loads that do not follow a daily load change pattern and changes are not correlated with the daily load change pattern.

AFElement.Name: NonConformLoadGroup
AFElement.Description: Loads that do not follow a daily and seasonal load variation pattern.

AFElement.Name: NonConformLoadSchedule
AFElement.Description: An active power (Y1-axis) and reactive power (Y2-axis) schedule (curves) versus time (X-axis) for non-conforming loads, e.g., large industrial load or power station service (where modeled)

AFElement.Name: OperationalLimit
AFElement.Description: A value associated with a specific kind of limit.

AFElement.Name: OperationalLimitSet
AFElement.Description: A set of limits associated with equipmnet.

AFElement.Name: PMU
AFElement.Description: A specialized IED that emits Synchrophasor information

AFElement.Name: PMU_Template_Base
AFElement.Description: A specialized IED that emits Synchrophasor information

AFElement.Name: PowerSystemResource
AFElement.Description: A power system resource can be an item of equipment such as a Switch, an EquipmentContainer containing many individual items of equipment such as a Substation, or an organisational entity such as Company or SubControlArea. This provides for the nesting of collections of PowerSystemResources within other PowerSystemResources. For example, a Switch could be a member of a Substation and a Substation could be a member of a division of a Company.

AFElement.Name: PowerTransformer
AFElement.Description: An electrical device consisting of two or more coupled windings, with or without a magnetic core, for introducing mutual coupling between electric circuits. Transformers can be used to control voltage and phase shift (active power flow).

AFElement.Name: ReactiveCapabilityCurve
AFElement.Description: Reactive power rating envelope versus the synchronous machine's active power, in both the generating and motoring modes. For each active power value there is a corresponding high and low reactive power limit value. Typically there will be a separate curve for each coolant condition, such as hydrogen pressure. The Y1 axis values represent reactive minimum and the Y2 axis values represent reactive maximum.

AFElement.Name: RegularIntervalSchedule
AFElement.Description: The schedule has TimePoints where the time between them is constant.

AFElement.Name: RegularTimePoint
AFElement.Description: TimePoints for a schedule where the time between the points is constant.

AFElement.Name: RegulatingCondEq
AFElement.Description: RegulatingCondEq is a type of ConductingEquipment that can regulate Measurements and have a RegulationSchedule.

AFElement.Name: RegulatingControl
AFElement.Description: Specifies a set of equipment that works together to control a power system quantity such as voltage or flow.

AFElement.Name: RegulationSchedule
AFElement.Description: A pre-established pattern over time for a controlled variable, e.g., busbar voltage.

AFElement.Name: RemoteUnit
AFElement.Description: A remote unit can be a RTU, IED, substation control system, control center etc. The communication with the remote unit can be through various standard protocols (e.g. IEC 61870, IEC 61850) or non standard protocols (e.g. DNP, RP570 etc.). A remote unit contain remote data points that might be telemetered, collected or calculated. The RemoteUnit class inherit PowerSystemResource. The intention is to allow RemotUnits to have Measurements. These Measurements can be used to model unit status as operational, out of service, unit failure etc.

AFElement.Name: Season
AFElement.Description: A specified time period of the year, e.g., Spring, Summer, Fall, Winter

AFElement.Name: SeasonDayTypeSchedule
AFElement.Description: The schedule specialize RegularIntervalSchedule with type curve data for a specific type of day and season. This means that curves of this type cover a 24 hour period.

AFElement.Name: SeriesCompensator
AFElement.Description: A Series Compensator is a series capacitor or reactor or an AC transmission line without charging susceptance.

AFElement.Name: ShuntCompensator
AFElement.Description: A shunt capacitor or reactor or switchable bank of shunt capacitors or reactors. A section of a shunt compensator is an individual capacitor or reactor. Negative values for mVArPerSection and nominalMVAr indicate that the compensator is a reactor.

AFElement.Name: SiscoModelAuthority
AFElement.Description: Model Authorities

AFElement.Name: SiscoUnresolvedInstance

AFElement.Name: StaticVarCompensator
AFElement.Description: A facility for providing variable and controllable shunt reactive power. The SVC typically consists of a stepdown transformer, filter, thyristor-controlled reactor, and thyristor-switched capacitor arms. The SVC may operate in fixed MVar output mode or in voltage control mode. When in voltage control mode, the output of the SVC will be proportional to the deviation of voltage at the controlled bus from the voltage setpoint. The SVC characteristic slope defines the proportion. If the voltage at the controlled bus is equal to the voltage setpoint, the SVC MVar output is zero.

AFElement.Name: StationSupply
AFElement.Description: Station supply with load derived from the station output.

AFElement.Name: SubFunction
AFElement.Description: A small portion of a task.

AFElement.Name: SubGeographicalRegion

AFElement.Name: SubLoadArea
AFElement.Description: The class is the second level in a hierarchical structure for grouping of loads for the purpose of load flow load scaling.

AFElement.Name: Substation
AFElement.Description: A collection of equipment for purposes other than generation or utilization, through which electric energy in bulk is passed for the purposes of switching or modifying its characteristics.

AFElement.Name: Switch
AFElement.Description: A generic device designed to close, or open, or both, one or more electric circuits.

AFElement.Name: SynchronousMachine
AFElement.Description: An electromechanical device that operates synchronously with the network. It is a single machine operating either as a generator or synchronous condenser or pump.

AFElement.Name: TapChanger

AFElement.Name: Terminal
AFElement.Description: An electrical connection point to a piece of conducting equipment. Terminals are connected at physical connection points called "connectivity nodes".

AFElement.Name: ThermalGeneratingUnit

AFElement.Name: TieFlow

AFElement.Name: TransformerWinding
AFElement.Description: A winding is associated with each defined terminal of a transformer (or phase shifter).

AFElement.Name: VoltageLevel
AFElement.Description: A collection of equipment at one common system voltage forming a switchgear. The equipment typically consist of breakers, busbars, instrumentation, control, regulation and protection devices as well as assemblies of all these.

AFElement.Name: VoltageLimit

AFElement.Name: IdentifiedObject.localName
AFElement.Description: The localName is a human readable name of the object. It is only used with objects organized in a naming hierarchy. The simplest naming hierarchy has just one parent (the root) giving a flat naming hierarchy. However, the naming hierarchy usually has several levels, e.g. Substation, VoltageLevel, Equipment etc. Children of the same parent have names that are unique among them. If the uniqueness requirement cannot be met IdentifiedObject.localName shall not be used, use IdentifiedObject.name instead.

AFElement.Name: IdentifiedObject.name

AFElement.Name: IdentifiedObject.pathName
